message.content: Yes, the authors include the necessary information and source code to replicate their experiments. They provide the GitHub link in Appendix G, as well as detailed information about their user study, hyperparameters, and training details, which can be found in various subsections of the Appendix. This allows readers to reproduce the main experimental results.

Yes, the authors include the necessary information needed to reproduce the main experimental results. They provide the source code, hyperparameters, training details, and user study instructions, and they also mention a URL (https://github.com/Stanford-ILIAD/teaching) where the code for the user study can be found. Furthermore, they refer to an additional visualizations page (https://sites.google.com/view/assistive-teaching-2022/home). Together, these resources should be sufficient for reproducing the main experimental results.

Yes, the authors include the necessary information to replicate the experiments, such as hyperparameters, training details, and environment pre-processing. Additionally, they provide the link to the source code on GitHub for both PARKING and WRITING environments, along with the trained CompILE models. This information can be found in the appendix section of the paper.
